commit.message: README: add notice about unmaintained software

README: update installation instructions

Fixes https://github.com/agordon/fastx_toolkit/pull/12 ,
      https://github.com/agordon/fastx_toolkit/issues/11 .

docs: update Galaxy's URLs

Suggested in https://github.com/agordon/fastx_toolkit/pull/16 .

sequence_alignment.h: add missing header

Should fix https://github.com/agordon/fastx_toolkit/issues/13 .

fastx_quality_stats: fix buffer overflow

Fixes https://github.com/agordon/fastx_toolkit/issues/17
Fixed wrong constants for [MIN|MAX]_QUALITY_VALUE; they are also used for checking the input instead of hardcoded numbers
Bumped version to 0.0.14

Merge pull request #2 from Debian/typo

Corrected a typo.
Corrected a typo.

build: detect TR1 or C++11 with automake macros.

Used in fastx-collapser, should ease compilation on newer systems.

fastx: improve ugly 'fgets' hack to avoid compilation warnings.

This change was already included in the previously released
version 0.0.13.2 (but I forgot to add it here).
Enables compiling with "-D_FORTIFY_SOURCE=2".

Solves github issue #1.
configure.ac: bugfix for CXXFLAGS
build: remove unneeded file from configure.ac
build: fix include path for 'make distcheck'.

Removed custom CSHL custom Galaxy XML files.

Nobody used them outside CSHL.

bugfix: invalid nucleotides were not properly detected.

Fixes http://bugs.debian.org/715888

BREAKING-CHANGE: disallow empty nucleotide strings.

Fail on FASTA/FASTX files with empty (zero-length)
nucleotide strings.
This might break old-pipelines, but those FASTAs are invalid
anyhow and processing them should not succeed.

Fixes: http://bugs.debian.org/715887
Updated Copyright year and contact email.

BREAKING-CHANGE: default quality is now Sanger(33)

Instead of Illumina (64). No need for "-Q33" anymore.
gitignore: add INSTALL
Added missing header, fix compilation issues.
Maint: improve autotools files
Maint: remove auto-generated files, add gitignore
Bumped version to 0.0.13, added build-scripts, hacked m4 STD::TR1 detection.
Hacked STD::TR1 check for missing files on CentOS 5.4
Makefile.am typo for fastq_quality_trimmer
Filename type: fastx instead of fastq (quality_trimmer)

Added/Updated functional tests for almost all the tools

Quality-Plot, Nucleotide-Distribution, Length-Distribution,
and Barcode-Splitter can not be reliably tested (so far).
More XML changes: make CUSTOM vs CSHL vesion even more similar.
XML updates: minor changes to make Public and CSHL versions easier to compare.
